## 6. API Design

### 6.1 Configuration Usage
```php
// Using custom configuration class
$config = new \HCart\LaravelMultiCart\Config\LaravelMultiCartConfig([
    'models' => [
        'cart' => \App\Models\CustomCart::class,
        'cart_item' => \App\Models\CustomCartItem::class,
    ],
    'callbacks' => [
        'unique_item' => function ($cartableId, $cartableType, $attributes) {
            // Custom uniqueness logic - include size and color in uniqueness
            $uniqueKey = $cartableId . $cartableType;
            if (isset($attributes['size'])) {
                $uniqueKey .= $attributes['size'];
            }
            if (isset($attributes['color'])) {
                $uniqueKey .= $attributes['color'];
            }
            return md5($uniqueKey);
        },
        'item_update' => function ($cartItem, $oldData, $newData) {
            // Log item updates
            \Log::info('Cart item updated', [
                'cart_id' => $cartItem->cart_id,
                'item_id' => $cartItem->id,
                'old_data' => $oldData,
                'new_data' => $newData
            ]);
        }
    ],
    'prevent_duplicates' => true,
    'tax_rate' => 0.08,
    'currency' => 'EUR'
]);

// Set configuration globally
LaravelMultiCart::setConfig($config);

// Or create cart with specific configuration
$cart = LaravelMultiCart::cart('shopping')->withConfig($config);
```

